<BaseLayout title="about · siddhant mody">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1 class="fade-in fade-in--1">about</h1>

    <div class="fade-in fade-in--2">
      {/* TODO: longer-form bio. write this in your own voice. */}
      <p>
        i'm a robotics m.s. + meche b.s. student at the university of pennsylvania,
        finishing both in may 2027. ultimately, i want to create end-to-end robots 
        that work in places people don't want to (or can't). i think about robots from the mechanical side first, 
        then the controls and embedded layers that make them work.
      </p>
      <p>
        {/* TODO: what do you actually care about? what gets you out of bed? */}
        i'm most interested in control problems where the mechanical design and the controller can't be separated -
        pushing, grasping, assembly, anywhere the standard "plan a move, execute a
        move" decomposition breaks down.
        the c3+ work i've been doing at DAIR is in this space, and my fascination 
        with industrial and field robotics comes from the same place, inspiring
        my future career goals.
      </p>
      <p>
        outside of school, i'm especially into music and sports (packers, hornets, hurricanes, and man united!). 
        when i have some spare time, you can also find me working on a machine-learning
        based stock trading algorithm at stockvocate or building biocomputing's
        true promise at laminae.
      </p>
    </div>

